This project was assigned as part of the Digital Literacy course to help students understand and apply essential digital skills. As a Student Digital Ambassador, the objective of this project was to create awareness about digital tools, online platforms, and safe digital practices among peers.

The project consists of five tasks, including creating an infographic, building a digital portfolio, exploring coding and collaboration platforms, understanding email etiquette, and studying cybercrime awareness. Each task provided practical exposure to important digital concepts and tools used in academic and professional environments.

Through this project, I gained knowledge about maintaining a professional online presence, using online platforms effectively, and staying safe in the digital world.
